OL,5,Ceconomy'
OL,7,FThe Foundation's housing outlook used
OL,8,FOCED data to compare the UK's housing
OL,9,Fissues against other similar economies.
OL,11,FIt said that while there is "limited
OL,12,Fcross-national data" on floorspace,
OL,13,Fhomes in England have less average
OL,14,Ffloorspace per person (38 m2) than
OL,15,Fmany similar countries, including the
OL,16,FUnited States (66 m2), Germany (46
OL,17,Fm2), France (43 m2) and Japan (40 m2).
