OL,5,Ceconomy'
OL,7,F"Britain's housing crisis is decades
OL,8,Fin the making, with successive
OL,9,Fgovernments failing to build enough
OL,10,Fnew homes and modernise our existing
OL,11,Fstock. That now has to change."
OL,13,FA Department for Levelling Up, Housing
OL,14,Fand Communities spokesperson said:
OL,15,F"Housebuilding is a Government
OL,16,Fpriority and despite global economic
OL,17,Fchallenges we remain on track to meet
OL,18,Fthe manifesto commitment of delivering
OL,19,Fone million homes this Parliament, and
OL,20,Fhave introduced reforms to improve the
OL,21,Fplanning system.
